  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer (Main Contractor)",
  "description": "<p>Be part of a <strong>leading main contractor</strong> with opportunities to contribute to <strong>roadworks, and LTA infrastructure projects</strong>. This role offers exposure to diverse and large-scale works, giving you the platform to sharpen your technical skills and accelerate your career.</p><p><strong>Why Join Us:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Exposure to <strong>landmark projects</strong>: infrastructure LTA works, roadworks</p></li><li><p>Clear pathways for <strong>career growth & development</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Competitive salary, benefits, and training support</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support the planning, coordination, and supervision of construction works.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with consultants, subcontractors, and site teams to ensure smooth operations.</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, safety, and quality compliance.</p></li><li><p>Assist with technical submissions, shop drawings, and documentation.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree/Diploma in <strong>Civil/Structural/Construction Engineering</strong> or related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Minimum of 2 years of experience in the civil engineering industry.</p></li><li><p>Proactive, hands-on, and strong problem-solving mindset.</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills and ability to work in teams.</p></li></ul><p>How to Apply:<br />Interested candidates, please submit your updated resume by using Quick Apply button<br />We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be informed.<br /></p><p>Yip Seow Thung<br />Registration Number: R24121304<br />EA License No: 18C902</p>",
